{"id":152,"date":"2007-11-09T15:48:20","date_gmt":"2007-11-09T23:48:20","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/site-news\/learncppcom-tutorials-now-with-syntax-highlighting\/"},"modified":"2007-11-09T15:48:20","modified_gmt":"2007-11-09T23:48:20","slug":"learncppcom-tutorials-now-with-syntax-highlighting","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/site-news\/learncppcom-tutorials-now-with-syntax-highlighting\/","title":{"rendered":"LearnCpp.com tutorials: Now with syntax highlighting!"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Yup, it&#8217;s finally here.  If you have a javascript enabled browser, code examples in the tutorials will now have line numbering and syntax highlighting.  For example, instead of:<\/p>\n<pre>\nCents&amp; Cents::operator= (const Cents &amp;cSource)\n{\n    \/\/ check for self-assignment by comparing the address of the\n    \/\/ implicit object and the parameter\n    if (this == &amp;cSource)\n        return *this;\n \n    \/\/ do the copy\n    m_nCents = cSource.m_nCents;\n \n    \/\/ return the existing object\n    return *this;\n}\n<\/pre>\n<p>you will now see:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"language-cpp line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-cpp match-braces\">Cents&amp; Cents::operator= (const Cents &amp;cSource)\n{\n    \/\/ check for self-assignment by comparing the address of the\n    \/\/ implicit object and the parameter\n    if (this == &amp;cSource)\n        return *this;\n \n    \/\/ do the copy\n    m_nCents = cSource.m_nCents;\n \n    \/\/ return the existing object\n    return *this;\n}<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>I am still working at converting the previous tutorials from the old-style to the new-style, and given that there are over 100 of them, it may take me a little while to get through all of them.<\/p>\n<p>If you try to mouse-select the syntax-highlighted code and paste it into another document (or compiler), you will also get line numbers.  Instead, use the &#8220;copy to clipboard&#8221; function at the top of the code snippet.  This will place the code in your clipboard, and you can paste it into another document like normal.<\/p>\n<p>If that doesn&#8217;t work for you, use &#8220;view plain&#8221;, which will show you the code without syntax highlighting and line numbers, and copy it from there in the normal manner.<\/p>\n<p>I hope you find that this change brings some added value to your CPP experience.<\/p>\n<p>Thanks for stopping by.<\/p>\n<p>-Alex<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Yup, it&#8217;s finally here. If you have a javascript enabled browser, code examples in the tutorials will now have line numbering and syntax highlighting. For example, instead of: Cents&amp; Cents::operator= (const Cents &amp;cSource) { \/\/ check for self-assignment by comparing the address of the \/\/ implicit object and the parameter &hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[2],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/152"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=152"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/152\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=152"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=152"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.learncpp.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=152"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}